A security officer who was shot in the head during an attack in Umlazi, south of Durban, on Monday has succumbed to his injuries. The man's colleague died at the scene of the shooting in B section. Both men were seated in a car when they came under fire. Emer-G-Med spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said the critically injured security officer was airlifted to a specialist facility. “The patient has sadly succumbed to his extensive injuries and died in hospital.” Police are investigating. TimesLIVE